{
  "texts": [
    "For example, a study assessing the sentiment of web-based conversations specifically related to local food and food banks found that the net sentiment was negative [82].",
    "In contrast, the Twitter posts in this study classified in topics related to food banks were largely positive.",
    "This is likely due to the type of discussion in the study by Jung et al [82] being dominated by negative words such as \"struggle,\" \"difficult,\" and \"desperate,\" whereas this study discussed more positive aspects, such as donations, support of food banks, and having access to these services.",
    "In addition, Scott et al [83] examined the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP) in the United States.",
    "These researchers found that news articles discussing the SNAP with extreme right media bias were more likely to score on either side of extreme sentiment [83]."
  ]
}